Vagal and glossopharyngeal sensory neurons include second-order chemosensory neurons that receive inputs from upstream sentinel cells, including glomus
cells, taste cells, NEBs, and enteroendocrine cells, as well as mechanosensory neurons that form IGLEs and end-net endings. Various neuron types project to
